hrow", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "childList": []}]}, {"text": ["So basically, PHP distinguishes between errors and exceptions.", "Errors haven't been modularized and made available to the user like they have been in Python.", "I believe that's related to the fact that PHP began as a collection of dynamic web scripts, grew and gained more features over time, and only more recently offered improved OOP support (i.e., version 5); whereas Python fundamentally supports OOP and other meta-functionality.", "And exception handling from the beginning."], "childNum": 2, "tag": "p", "senID": 1, "childList": [{"text": "collection of dynamic web scripts", "tag": "a", "pos": 2, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://us.php.net/manual/en/history.php.php"}, {"text": "from the beginning", "tag": "a", "pos": 3, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/History_of_Python"}]}, {"text": ["Here's an example usage (again, a throw is necessary, or else nothing will be caught):"], "childNum": 1, "tag": "p", "senID": 2, "childList": [{"text": "throw", "childNum": 0, "tag": "code", "pos": 0, "childList": []}]}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n function oops($a)\n{\n    if (!$a) {\n        throw new Exception('empty variable');\n    }\n    return \"oops, $a\";\n}\n\ntry {\n    print oops($b);\n} catch (Exception $e) {\n    print \"Error occurred: \" . $e-&gt;getMessage();\n}\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 3}], [{"text": ["You can handle PHP errors like they were exceptions by using set_error_handler"], "childNum": 1, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": [{"text": "set_error_handler", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://www.php.net/manual/en/function.set-error-handler.php"}]}, {"text": ["In this error handler function you can throw various exception, according to error level for instance."], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 1, "childList": []}, {"text": ["By doing this you can treat any error (including programming errors) in a common way."], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 2, "childList": []}], [{"text": ["PHP 5 has the exception model:"], "childNum": 1, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": [{"text": "exception model", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://au2.php.net/manual/en/language.exceptions.php"}]}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n try {\n    print 'stuff';\n} catch (Exception $e) {\n    echo 'Caught exception: ',  $e-&gt;getMessage(), \"\\n\";\n}\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 1}], [{"text": ["Assuming you're trying to catch exceptions, take a look at http://php.net/manual/en/language.exceptions.php"], "childNum": 1, "tag": "p", "senID": 0, "childList": [{"text": "http://php.net/manual/en/language.exceptions.php", "tag": "a", "pos": 0, "childList": [], "childNum": 0, "href": "http://php.net/manual/en/language.exceptions.php"}]}, {"text": ["You could try something like"], "childNum": 0, "tag": "p", "senID": 1, "childList": []}, {"code": "<pre>\n<code>\n try {\necho \"Stuff\";\n} catch (Exception $e) {\necho \"Something Else\";\n}\n</code>\n</pre>\n", "senID": 2}]]